        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(skills): add full service overview to gog SKILL.md (fixes #94943)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe `gog` SKILL.md bundled with OpenClaw only documents 6 Google services (Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Contacts, Sheets, Docs), but the `gogcli` CLI now supports 20+ services including YouTube, Maps, Forms, Meet, Classroom, Chat, and more. Agents using the bundled skill have no visibility into these capabilities.\n\nFixes #94943\n\n## Changes\n\n- Updated description to list all supported services\n- Added a **Supported Services** table with key commands per service\n- Added **Additional capabilities** section (MCP server, Drive audits, Gmail filters, Workspace admin)\n- Added **Full Command Reference** section pointing to `gog --help` and gogcli.sh docs\n- Fixed section headings to use proper Markdown `##` format\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** gog SKILL.md now documents all 20+ services supported by gogcli\n- **Environment tested:** macOS, Node v24, openclaw@2026.6.8\n- **Steps run after the patch:** `pnpm build` + `grep -c \"YouTube\\|Maps\\|Forms\\|Meet\\|Classroom\" skills/gog/SKILL.md`\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```\n$ grep -c \"YouTube\\|Maps\\|Forms\\|Meet\\|Classroom\" skills/gog/SKILL.md\n12\n$ grep \"description:\" skills/gog/SKILL.md\ndescription: \"Google Workspace CLI for Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Docs, Sheets, Sites, Slides, Forms, Meet, Apps Script, Analytics, Search Console, Contacts, Tasks, People, Classroom, Chat, YouTube, and Workspace admin.\"\n$ pnpm build\n... (build succeeds)\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** SKILL.md includes all 20+ services with key commands, proper headings, and full command reference links\n- **What was not tested:** Runtime gog CLI behavior (docs-only change)\n\n- [x] AI-assisted (Hermes Agent)\n",
